WEBVTT

00:02.711 --> 00:05.505
McQUEEN AND MATER: (SINGING)
<i>Crank shaft's connected to the flywheel</i>

00:05.797 --> 00:07.924
(BOTH SCATTING)

00:08.008 --> 00:10.176
You know, if we poured it on at top speed,

00:10.260 --> 00:12.846
we'd be in town for the wedding
in a day and a half.

00:12.929 --> 00:14.806
(GROANS) Don't remind me.

00:14.889 --> 00:18.018
Thousands of things to see,
you have to bring up nuptials?

00:18.101 --> 00:19.227
Nobody cares about...

00:19.310 --> 00:20.353
Uh... Where is the road?

00:20.729 --> 00:23.273
You know, I was starting
to wonder about that myself.

00:23.440 --> 00:27.610
Well, hey, there's nobody else out here.
We can go as fast as we want.

00:27.694 --> 00:28.695
(ENGINE REVVING)

00:28.778 --> 00:30.071
-Want to race?
-Uh...

00:30.155 --> 00:31.781
-Well...
-Come on!

00:31.865 --> 00:34.534
Ha! Look at you, all charged up to race.

00:34.617 --> 00:36.619
But I don't have a chance against... Go!

00:36.703 --> 00:38.329
-(MATER WHOOPING)
-Ha-ha!

00:39.956 --> 00:41.332
Come on, McQueen!

00:44.085 --> 00:45.420
-MATER: Whoo!
-Whoa!

00:46.087 --> 00:47.630
-Yeah, buddy!
-Whoo! Yeah!

00:48.173 --> 00:49.466
Oh, man.

00:49.549 --> 00:53.011
I ain't the quickest,
but it sure would be fun to be fast.

00:53.094 --> 00:55.096
(ENGINE BUZZING IN DISTANCE)

00:55.180 --> 00:56.181
What is that?

00:57.515 --> 00:59.726
It sounds like an airplane?

00:59.809 --> 01:02.562
Oh, maybe it's one of them fancy
delivery drones.

01:02.854 --> 01:04.689
-(GASPS) Look out!
-(MATER YELPS)

01:05.065 --> 01:06.649
Holy smokes!

01:06.733 --> 01:09.444
That, sir, was no delivery drone.

01:10.445 --> 01:14.365
<i>Hitting the highway, a couple of friends</i>

01:14.449 --> 01:18.244
<i>With new adventures 'round every bend</i>

01:18.328 --> 01:21.998
<i>Whether racing fast or getting towed</i>

01:22.332 --> 01:26.628
<i>Ever together, cars on the road</i>

01:29.923 --> 01:32.884
ANNOUNCER: <i>There's a lot of us today,</i>
<i>folks. Right now...</i>

01:32.967 --> 01:35.595
(LAUGHS) Land speed racers.

01:35.678 --> 01:37.722
So that's who almost
clipped us back there.

01:37.806 --> 01:38.807
Hey, look at that.

01:43.228 --> 01:45.063
Watch out for the Speed Demon.

01:45.146 --> 01:46.356
(CROWD CHEERING)

01:46.815 --> 01:48.233
Speed Demon?

01:48.316 --> 01:51.277
They've got their own language out here.
Their own culture even.

01:51.361 --> 01:53.863
With these cars,
everything gets stripped away.

01:53.947 --> 01:55.073
It's pure speed.

01:55.156 --> 01:56.950
Good time, Lou. You broke your record.

01:57.075 --> 01:59.202
Yeah, broke something. (CHUCKLES)

01:59.285 --> 02:01.246
With just the tiniest little
taste of death.

02:01.329 --> 02:03.331
FEMALE TRUCK: Out of the way!
Pardon me, please!

02:03.498 --> 02:06.459
Big long car coming through.
Watch it. Long car.

02:06.543 --> 02:09.921
Whoa! It's about breaking through.
It's a race against yourself.

02:10.338 --> 02:11.673
Check out the divisions.

02:11.756 --> 02:15.844
You've got your classic rod, your imports,
special construction, diesel trucks,

02:15.927 --> 02:17.220
rocket-powered cars.

02:17.303 --> 02:18.346
It's crazy.

02:18.429 --> 02:21.141
-They probably even have a ranking for...
-MALE CAR: Tow truck?

02:21.224 --> 02:22.976
I don't normally spend my time

02:23.059 --> 02:26.354
trying to mold the likes of you
into a racing machine.

02:26.437 --> 02:27.730
Oh, nuts and bolts!

02:27.814 --> 02:32.777
That said, we suddenly find ourselves
with a rare opening on our team.

02:34.696 --> 02:35.697
(GASPS)

02:35.780 --> 02:39.367
And so, you may accept
the privilege of racing for me.

02:39.450 --> 02:41.995
No, no, no, no, no, no.
We are just passing...

02:42.078 --> 02:43.705
Absofantastilutely!

02:43.788 --> 02:44.873
What? No.

02:44.956 --> 02:47.667
Perfect. Let's begin your journey.

02:47.750 --> 02:50.253
Mater, why are you doing this?

02:50.336 --> 02:52.881
I've always wanted
to go faster than fast.

02:52.964 --> 02:55.884
Shoot, right now, I've got
a pretty good shot at it.

02:56.342 --> 02:58.511
But what do we know about these crackpots?

02:59.179 --> 03:03.600
Uh, I mean, these perfectly reasonable
racing professionals.

03:04.100 --> 03:05.101
(SIGHS)

03:05.185 --> 03:06.477
(MECHANICAL WHIRRING)

03:06.561 --> 03:08.188
(METALLIC CREAKING)

03:08.271 --> 03:09.939
(WHIRRING CONTINUES)

03:12.525 --> 03:13.735
(LOUD THUD)

03:13.818 --> 03:15.278
(ENGINE POWERING UP)

03:17.530 --> 03:18.531
Whoa!

03:19.240 --> 03:20.700
MATER: Whoo-hoo!

03:21.659 --> 03:23.703
Dadgum! Look at me!

03:24.662 --> 03:27.081
Come on! Let's talk about this, buddy.

03:27.207 --> 03:30.001
I'm faster than fast
and quicker than quick.

03:30.668 --> 03:32.754
Watch out for the Speed Demon.

03:32.837 --> 03:33.838
(LAUGHING)

03:34.047 --> 03:35.465
(MATER WHOOPING)

03:35.548 --> 03:36.549
Oh, no.

03:36.633 --> 03:37.634
Mater!

03:39.135 --> 03:40.637
Whee-hoo!

03:40.970 --> 03:42.513
(LAUGHING)

03:45.475 --> 03:46.601
Mater!

03:50.021 --> 03:51.940
175 miles per hour.

03:52.023 --> 03:54.317
Okay, you did it, buddy!

03:54.609 --> 03:56.277
You can back off now.

03:56.361 --> 03:57.362
Mater?

03:57.445 --> 03:59.781
I am speed!

04:01.324 --> 04:02.325
Whoa!

04:02.533 --> 04:04.202
(CACKLES)

04:06.204 --> 04:08.915
465 miles per hour.

04:08.998 --> 04:11.751
640 miles per hour.

04:12.293 --> 04:13.294
(BOOMS)

04:13.378 --> 04:14.379
(GASPS)

04:15.421 --> 04:16.923
(WHOOPING)

04:17.006 --> 04:18.758
-(DEVICE BEEPING)
-(MATER LAUGHING)

04:24.472 --> 04:25.682
Uh-oh.

04:25.765 --> 04:26.766
(SCREAMING)

04:33.815 --> 04:34.816
(YELPS)

04:36.734 --> 04:38.778
(GASPS) What the... Dadgum!

04:38.987 --> 04:39.988
(YELPS)

04:40.280 --> 04:42.282
Well, that's it, then.

04:42.365 --> 04:44.117
Wait. That's what then?

04:44.200 --> 04:45.868
I'll take you the rest of the way.

04:45.952 --> 04:47.620
What the... Who are you?

04:48.538 --> 04:50.873
The racers call me the Speed Demon.

04:50.957 --> 04:52.250
Part of the local lore.

04:52.333 --> 04:54.752
You know, "Watch out for the Speed Demon."

04:54.836 --> 04:57.630
Shoot! You don't look
all that demon-y to me.

04:57.714 --> 04:59.173
Ha! Tell me about it.

04:59.841 --> 05:01.301
Well, this has been a treat.

05:01.384 --> 05:03.261
-I guess I'll just be...
-Mater.

05:03.344 --> 05:05.388
What the heck are you doing out here?

05:05.471 --> 05:08.266
(SIGHS) Just scratching an itch.

05:08.474 --> 05:13.438
Thinking, "Why can't I be the fastest?
Why can't I be the best at something?"

05:14.022 --> 05:17.108
Well, I never thought
this is how you'd go out.

05:18.234 --> 05:21.237
Honestly, this seems about right.

05:21.946 --> 05:23.823
Okay, then. Shall we be going?

05:23.906 --> 05:24.907
What, now?

05:24.991 --> 05:28.202
But who's going to break it to Lightning?

05:28.786 --> 05:29.912
He'll figure it out.

05:31.247 --> 05:33.207
I don't even get to say goodbye?

05:33.291 --> 05:34.792
Do you know what a seance is?

05:34.876 --> 05:35.877
Wait, wait, wait.

05:35.960 --> 05:37.253
We play checkers for it.

05:37.337 --> 05:38.796
I win, you send me back.

05:38.880 --> 05:42.050
There's no sending back.
What's done is done.

05:42.133 --> 05:44.218
Ooh. How about we match wits?

05:44.469 --> 05:47.555
Uh... What number am I thinking of now?

05:47.638 --> 05:49.223
Mater, that's not how it works.

05:49.307 --> 05:50.767
-Seven.
-Dang. You're right.

05:50.850 --> 05:51.851
-Yes!
-Okay.

05:51.934 --> 05:53.728
How about this? Close your eyes.

05:53.811 --> 05:55.855
How many tires am I holding up?

05:55.938 --> 05:57.940
Well, it can't be more than four.

05:58.024 --> 05:59.692
You have six tires, right?

05:59.817 --> 06:01.944
Well, was it four or six?

06:02.737 --> 06:04.781
Hey, where'd you... Hey.

06:04.864 --> 06:06.115
(MATER LAUGHING)

06:06.532 --> 06:07.909
(GRUNTING)

06:07.992 --> 06:09.160
Come on.

06:09.243 --> 06:11.120
Well, that's a novel approach.

06:13.956 --> 06:14.957
Shoot.

06:15.833 --> 06:16.834
(LAUGHS)

06:18.044 --> 06:21.589
Ah, well, I suppose I can let one
slip through the cracks.

06:22.715 --> 06:23.883
(SCREAMING)

06:34.602 --> 06:35.603
Whoa.

06:35.686 --> 06:37.063
What was that?

06:37.146 --> 06:39.524
Mater. You're alive!

06:39.607 --> 06:41.317
(LAUGHS) I do believe I am.

06:43.444 --> 06:45.780
You was worried about me, wasn't you, huh?

06:46.030 --> 06:48.366
Ha-ha! Come on. You was worried.

06:48.449 --> 06:50.201
Of course I was, you big lug-nut.

06:50.284 --> 06:52.036
We're best buddies, aren't we?

06:52.120 --> 06:54.997
Besides, what fun is a road trip
on your own anyway?

06:55.206 --> 06:56.749
You've got that right.

06:56.833 --> 06:58.167
-MALE CAR: Tow truck!
-(GASPS)

06:58.709 --> 07:01.129
Do you know what you did, tow truck?

07:01.254 --> 07:02.505
Records have been shattered.

07:02.588 --> 07:04.841
This is just the beginning.
We'll make history.

07:04.924 --> 07:06.717
Tow truck and me, partners even.

07:06.801 --> 07:08.928
Hey, there he is!
Tow truck, wanna race for me?

07:09.011 --> 07:10.847
You were incredible.
You should race for us!

07:10.930 --> 07:12.640
Listen to me, you're a legend, tow truck!

07:12.723 --> 07:14.517
Uh... Race you to the next town?

07:14.600 --> 07:17.395
Oh, come on. You know
I don't have a chance against... Go!

07:18.146 --> 07:20.898
-Tow truck, we're not done!
-Where you going, tow truck?

07:22.817 --> 07:26.195
Whew. Okay, so what have
we learned here today?

07:26.279 --> 07:29.449
Well, turns out steering in a crosswind
at 700-and-change

07:29.532 --> 07:32.869
while tachometer's redlining
should be mostly avoided.

07:33.369 --> 07:34.579
Mostly.
